onal structure with the name of the deceased, the epithets  (for which, see Korhonen 2004: 84) and the indication of the age, with the verb  in the aorist form. Following Korhonen, the phonetic reading  for  seems to be less probable than  or  (from ): for a similar form, see Libertini NSA 1931: 391-392 (). Also the reading  seems to be less probable (despite  of the Christian epitaph Libertini 1931: 45 nr. 10) than the phonetic reading  (i.g. ): see IC IV 168*. The Doricism at l. 3 and the hypercorrection at l. 4 denote the stonecutter’s quest for refinement or poor knowledge of Greek (as also revealed by  of l. 5).",[524,526,528,530,532,534,536,538,540,542,544,545,547],{"_":525,"xml:lang":115},"χρηστὰ καὶ ἄμεμπτος",{"_":527,"xml:lang":115},"ζάω",{"_":529,"xml:lang":115},"αἴζως",{"_":531,"xml:lang":115},"ἔζης",{"_":533,"xml:lang":115},"αἴζωσ’",{"_":535,"xml:lang":115},"αἴζωσ(εν)",{"_":537,"xml:lang":115},"ζώω",{"_":539,"xml:lang":115},"ἔσζω[σ-]",{"_":541,"xml:lang":115},"ἔτι α εἴκοσι",{"_":543,"xml:lang":115},"ἔτι",{"_":485,"xml:lang":115},{"_":546,"xml:lang":115},"ἔτεα",{"_":485,"xml:lang":115},{"type":549,"listBibl":550},"bibliography",[551,579],{"type":118,"bibl":552},[553,556,559,562,565,570,573,576],{"author":121,"date":122,"citedRange":123,"ptr":554,"ref":555},{"target":125},{"_":127,"target":127},{"author":121,"date":131,"citedRange":132,"ptr":557,"ref":558},{"target":134},{"_":136,"target":136},{"author":140,"date":141,"citedRange":142,"ptr":560,"ref":561},{"target":144},{"_":146,"target":146},{"author":150,"date":151,"citedRange":152,"ptr":563,"ref":564},{"target":154},{"_":156,"target":156},{"type":160,"n":161,"citedRange":566,"ptr":568,"ref":569},{"ref":567},{"_":164,"target":165},{"target":167},{"_":169,"target":169},{"type":160,"n":173,"citedRange":174,"ptr":571,"ref":572},{"target":176},{"_":178,"target":178},{"type":160,"n":182,"citedRange":183,"ptr":574,"ref":575},{"target":185},{"_":187,"target":187},{"type":160,"n":191,"citedRange":192,"ptr":577,"ref":578},{"target":194},{"_":196,"target":196},{"type":200,"bibl":53},[581],{"n":447,"url":95,"height":448,"width":449,"desc":96,"surfaceType":444},{"title":583,"body":584,"divs":585,"images":601},"ISic001313. Epitaph for Markia Loukilia","  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001313_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001313_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001313.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001313-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"edition\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div\">\u003Ca id=\"al1\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΜΑΡΚΙΑ\u003Cbr id=\"al2\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΛΟΥΚΙΛΙΑ\u003Cbr id=\"al3\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΧΡΗΣΤΑΚΑΙΑ\u003Cbr id=\"al4\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ΜΕΜΤΟΣΑΙΖΩΣ\u003Cbr id=\"al5\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>ΕΤΙΑΕΙΚΟΣΙ´\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">l.3 reg., orig. ἄμεμτος | l.4 reg., orig. ΑΙΖΩΣαἴζωσ | l.5 reg., orig. ΕΤΙΑἔτια\u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photographs\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 4\">line.4: \u003Cspan>Torremuzza, Ferrara, Bertucci, Franz, Kaibel, Collitz-Bechtel: αἴζως (i.e. ἔζης); Korhonen: αἴζωσ(εν)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 5\">line.5: \u003Cspan>Torremuzza, Ferrara, Bertucci, Franz ἔτι α εἴκοσι; Kaibel, Collitz-Bechtel, Korhonen: ἔτια\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Markia Loukilia, honest and blameless, lived for 20 years.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Markia Loukilia, onesta e irreprensibile, visse 20 anni.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The epitaph has the traditional structure with the name of the deceased, the epithets \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">χρηστὰ καὶ ἄμεμπτος\u003C/span> (for which, see Korhonen 2004: 84) and the indication of the age, with the verb \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ζάω\u003C/span> in the aorist form. Following Korhonen, the phonetic reading \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">αἴζως\u003C/span> for \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἔζης\u003C/span> seems to be less probable than \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">αἴζωσ’\u003C/span> or \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">αἴζωσ(εν)\u003C/span> (from \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ζώω\u003C/span>): for a similar form, see Libertini NSA 1931: 391-392 (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἔσζω[σ-]\u003C/span>). Also the reading \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἔτι α εἴκοσι\u003C/span> seems to be less probable (despite \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἔτι\u003C/span> of the Christian epitaph Libertini 1931: 45 nr. 10) than the phonetic reading \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἔτια\u003C/span> (i.g. \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἔτεα\u003C/span>): see IC IV 168*. The Doricism at l. 3 and the hypercorrection at l. 4 denote the stonecutter’s quest for refinement or poor knowledge of Greek (as also revealed by \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἔτια\u003C/span> of l. 5).\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli> Castelli 1769 175 n. 69 \u003Ca href=\"http